 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umillwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Millwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 8:01:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wuss</span><hr size=1> Vendicare, I know what ye mean<br>
<br>
Patch Message February 21, 2000:<br>
Pickpocket now works to a max of 5 levels below you, or level 45...whichever is greater... You can pickpocket NPC up to level 55 if you are level 60.<br>
<br>
So, when you're in the planes, I can tell you mobs there are at LEAST level 47(think 48 actually), and therefore groups shouldn't even be worried about it unless the rogue is lvl 50+.<br>
If the rogue is, for example 49, 49-5=44, although the flat level 45 is the &quot;greater&quot;; no mob in planes are that low.  Once a rogue hits 51, he can go over the 45 hump, but it's still 5 less than his level... I'd say in the planes, you shouldn't worry about a rogue till he's about 53 or 54.<br>
<br>
THAT said, the following mobs are unpickable:<br>
Undead(spectre, skels, ghosts, vampires,etc), bugs(scarabs) in sebilis, or any other specific mob flagged as unpickable(like the wolves in PoG, and i guess the sebilis scarabs).<br>
<br>
Consider the 4d(some call it the crypt)/Emporer area in sebilis.  Once you pass the locked door, EVERYTHING is undead except the golems and they never have loot.. so don't get ants in your pants in that area about the rogue in your group.<br>
<br>
And the mobs that come to mind that do the &quot;stop thief&quot; type message are guards(altho only when they catch ye), bandits, dervs.. not sure if gnolls do.<br>
<br>
another thing to think about is WHAT can be pp'd; non-magic items, although i'm not sure about items that are equipped(such as weapons).  I never recall ever pickpocketing a weapon from a mob...  I'd GUESS if an item is equipped by a mob, you won't be able to PP it.  Strangely, I found it odd that verant chose NOT to make the Nephrite and i think the Flawed Sea Sapp magic item.  All the other quest gets are MAGIC ITEM, specifically so they can't be pickpocketed(which yes, i have managed to PP a nephrite).<br>
<br>
As for the person asking about how we fit a PP button into our combat.. that's where ye went wrong.  Don't make a PP button on your Combat buttons.  Go to your &quot;abilities&quot; and make a button there for pickpocket.<br>
THEN you make a hotkey button called &quot;PP/EVD&quot; and the commandlines go like this:<br>
/attack off<br>
/doability #<br>
/doability #<br>
/attack on<br>
<br>
Now the 2 #'s are for the numerical button of your ability buttons you made for pickpocket and Hide.  Personally, I have mine set to evade first, then pickpocket; reason is, it's hard to evade if you're getting hit, but you definately can't PP while hit, therefore best to evade to get the aggro off you so you CAN pickpocket<br>
And this hotbutton is very quick and hardly notice any delay in my swinging(provided you learn the pattern to time the usage right). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umillwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Millwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 8:08:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wuss</span><hr size=1> gonna make a followup remark.. one zone i think where EVERYTHING should be unpickable is Ssra temple.  I was SHOCKED to see &quot;you have stolen: a spell: Blessed Armor of the Risen&quot;.  a level 58 cleric spell!!!!<br>
<br>
